[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hello! I have been lurking in this Zulip (and on the mailing list) for some time and am finally ready to contribute :)</p>\n<p>To get my developmentt environment set up I consulted the official kernel docs around Rust, as well as Wedson's Linux Foundation mentorship session, and searched in this Zulip when I ran into issues.</p>\n<p>This process seems to be working well for me setting up the workstation and compiling the kernel</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://gist.github.com/nellshamrell/fa82173c59fc3b7dbb47a58d63aadade\">https://gist.github.com/nellshamrell/fa82173c59fc3b7dbb47a58d63aadade</a></p>\n<p>However, I am having some trouble running tests (using the commands in <a href=\"https://docs.kernel.org/rust/general-information.html\">this kernel doc</a>)</p>\n<p>I'm getting the error:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">No</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rule</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">to</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">target</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">'</span><span class=\"na\">rusttest</span><span class=\"o\">'</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Is it possible I'm missing something in my setup, or setting something up incorrectly?</p>",
        "id": 428027239,
        "sender_full_name": "Nell Shamrell-Harrington",
        "timestamp": 1710974585
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Are you able to compile anything rust-related in the kernel, like samples? Since a few months ago getting Rust enabled needed some standard dependencies disabled, and it makes setting up trickier</p>",
        "id": 428034322,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1710978496
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I will give that a try!</p>",
        "id": 428034706,
        "sender_full_name": "Nell Shamrell-Harrington",
        "timestamp": 1710978750
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Usually it's easiest to configure with <code>make menuconfig</code> if you aren't already doing that. Just see if rust samples show up and if not, search for <code>RUST</code> (<code>/</code>) and make sure it says the dependencies are set</p>",
        "id": 428034888,
        "sender_full_name": "Trevor Gross",
        "timestamp": 1710978866
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I am about to head out for the day, but I will give that a try tomorrow</p>",
        "id": 428034986,
        "sender_full_name": "Nell Shamrell-Harrington",
        "timestamp": 1710978933
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Finally back to this:</p>\n<p>This is what I see when checking whether Rust is available</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">azureuser</span><span class=\"o\">@</span><span class=\"n\">nell</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"n\">vm</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">03</span><span class=\"o\">-</span><span class=\"mi\">20</span>:<span class=\"o\">~/</span><span class=\"n\">linux</span><span class=\"cp\">$</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">rustavailable</span>\n<span class=\"n\">Rust</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">is</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">available</span><span class=\"o\">!</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Yet when I open the menuconfig with</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">sudo</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">LLVM</span><span class=\"o\">=</span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">make</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">menuconfig</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>And search for Rust, this is what I see.</p>\n<p><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/Q7Df_0Ii_qCT7mhbpqlnd5mS/image.png\">image.png</a></p>\n<div class=\"message_inline_image\"><a href=\"/user_uploads/35136/Q7Df_0Ii_qCT7mhbpqlnd5mS/image.png\" title=\"image.png\"><img src=\"/user_uploads/35136/Q7Df_0Ii_qCT7mhbpqlnd5mS/image.png\"></a></div><p>Which I'm interpreting as:</p>\n<p>HAVE_RUST is set to \"n\" when it should be \"y\"<br>\nRUST_IS_AVAILABLE = \"n\" when it should be \"y\"</p>\n<p>Checking the config file itself</p>",
        "id": 428220820,
        "sender_full_name": "Nell Shamrell-Harrington",
        "timestamp": 1711056446
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>neither of those values are present in .config</p>",
        "id": 428220976,
